o I get Windows Phone 8.1? What's changed in Windows Phone 8.1? Why have Facebook contacts and calendar stopped updating on my Windows Phone 8? What's Word Flow and how can I use it to type faster? How do I prevent my child from making purchases from the Store? What's Wi-Fi Sense? What types of files are included in the "other" phone storage category? How do I get contacts onto my phone? How do I copy my iTunes music to my phone? How do I move or sync music, photos, and videos between my computer and my phone? How do I add ringtones to my phone? How do I set up My Family to accept the Store Terms of Use and turn on app and game downloads for my child? How can I accept the Xbox Terms of Use so my child can download Xbox games on the phone? How do I project my phone onto another screen? How do I switch from Android or iPhone to Windows Phone? How can I find my lost phone? How do I back up my phone? How do I pair a Bluetooth accessory with my phone? Where are my installed apps? How do I reinstall apps I've purchased? What's a Microsoft account and why do I need one? What do the icons on my phone mean? Features, apps, and services are subject to change and may not be available depending on where you live, your service provider, device, or Windows Phone software version. A Microsoft account, network connectivity, and data service contract may be required to use certain features; fees may apply. Phone pricing determined by the seller or service provider. A service contract may be required and other restrictions may apply. For developers | For business | Careers | Site map | Contact us | Follow Privacy & cookies | Terms of Use | Trademarks | United States (English) | Mobile © 2016 Microsoft
